  "prompt": "How do I have to pay the installments once I bought something through krazybee?",
  "response": "When you purchase something through KrazyBee and opt for installment payments, you typically follow these steps to pay your installments:\n\n1. **Payment Schedule**:  \n   KrazyBee will provide you with a payment schedule, including the due dates and the amount for each installment. This information is usually available on the app or website.\n\n2. **Payment Methods**:  \n   - **Auto-Debit**: KrazyBee may automatically deduct the installment amount from the linked bank account on the due date.  \n   - **Manual Payment**: You can manually pay the installment through the app or website using options like UPI, debit/credit card, net banking, or wallet.  \n   - **Offline Payment**: In some cases, you might be able to pay through offline methods like cash deposit at specified bank branches.\n\n3. **Reminders**:  \n   KrazyBee usually sends reminders (via SMS, email, or app notifications) before the due date to ensure you don\u2019t miss a payment.\n\n4. **Late Fees**:  \n   Make sure to pay on time to avoid late fees or penalties. If you miss a payment, contact KrazyBee customer support to resolve the issue.\n\n5. **Track Payments**:  \n   You can track your payment history and outstanding installments through the KrazyBee app or website.\n\nIf you have any specific queries about your payment plan, it\u2019s best to check the app or contact KrazyBee\u2019s customer support for assistance.",
